# Features & Permissions — source is yabala-fe

Source of truth: `/Users/yeasirarafat/projects/yabala-fe`.

This app is the mobile version of the `admin` and `manager` panels of the Yabala
web frontend. To learn what a screen contains or needs, read the matching web route:

- Admin: `yabala-fe/app/admin/**` (and its `components/`)
- Manager: `yabala-fe/app/manager/**` (and its `components/`)

## Role model

From `yabala-fe/middleware.ts`, `user_type` is either `admin` or `manager`:

- **admin** — full access. Sections: `(analytics)` (customer-analytics,
  sales-analytics), `(menu)`, `(order)`, `(promotion)`, `(seo)`, `(settings)`, `(user)`
- **manager** — subset. Sections: `(menu)`, `(order)`

Build navigation, screens, and permission gating so a manager only sees the
manager subset and an admin sees everything, matching the web behavior.

Before building a feature, confirm which role(s) can access it in the web app,
and replicate that gating here (e.g. based on the authenticated user's role).
